N2  - This article illustrates the importance of imperfect information in self-enforcing trade agreements. It shows that expected welfare is higher with current period uncertainty, and?a high level?of uncertainty may?even?undermine the need for a safeguard clause. These results were derived by extending the seminal paper by Bagwell and Staiger (The American Economic Review?80 (1990), 779?95) to account for current period uncertainty.
ER  - 

