SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2009.00578.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the properties of the generalized stochastic gradient (GSG) learning in forward-looking models. GSG algorithms are a natural and convenient way to model learning when agents allow for parameter drift or robustness to parameter uncertainty in their beliefs. The conditions for convergence of GSG learning to a rational expectations equilibrium are distinct from but related to the well-known stability conditions for least squares learning.
ER  - 

